    "explanation": "More て-form patterns. 少し待って、よくきく — wait a bit, then listen carefully. Two actions linked by て.\n\nRequests continue: こちらへきて！ どうぞ、たべて。 A bare て-form addressed to someone is a request.\n\nNotice さあ行ってみて — go and try seeing. て + みる = 'try doing.' This pattern builds on the linking function of て.\n\nRe-read and watch for て + みる. What is being tried?"
